        <td bgcolor="#DbDdB3" colspan="2" valign="top"><img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="midnightblue" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="1">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;07/12/2001&nbsp;:&nbsp; 9:04:43 PM</font>

        
		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&id=26"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=26')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_messengers.asp?mode=ICQ&ICQ=1984232&M_NAME=Borlanis')"><img src="http://online.mirabilis.com/scripts/online.dll?icq=1984232&img=5" height=15 width=15 alt="Send Borlanis an ICQ Message" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&TOPIC_ID=1229&FORUM_ID=19&CAT_ID=8&Forum_Title=Tales+and+Stories+of+Adventure&Topic_Title=Adventure+of+a+Lifetime+part+1"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="midnightblue" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> A long time ago a young barbarian was learning the ways of a shaman in the cold, cruel hills of the tundra in Everfrost.  As a youth of 10 seasons he had overstretched himself in battling a mammoth calf.  Believing that a strategic retreat was in order, he headed towards the friendly guards of the pass.  Alas the guards were able to dispatch the calf but not before it had delivered the telling blow sending the barbarian youth back to his naked beginnings.  </P><P>Upon returning to the scene of the unfortunate encounter the barbarian lad was horrified.  For where his battered former self should lie, with his hard earned leather armor ----  there was nothing!!!  Just as he was beginning to lament about his loss, a spry little elf girl happened by.  Being young he assumed that as elves could track she might be able to help.  Alas, her talent lay in finding things with live, beating hearts. However she said she had mighty barbarian friend that was coming along and perhaps he could help.  The barbarian shaman appeared, dressed in such finery that the younger shaman had only dreamt about.   He comforted the lad and told him to hold steady and he would see what he could do.  Shortly after the young shaman was greeted with the announcement that his armor had been found!!!</P><P>This was the young shaman Borlanis' introduction to the mighty shaman Bearpaws and his charasmatic elf sidekick, Heavan.  They were both leaders of the family clan of Amber and young Borlanis voiced his desire to become part of that family.  He had met one other of the family by the name of Stradd, who had provided him with much help and some armor.  Completing the requirements young Borlanis was admitted to the Order of Amber and it was one of the most proud moments in his young life.</P><P>Through the years Borlanis learned much from the mighty Bearpaws and others of the family of Amber.  The names are to numerous to mention but the names of some can not be passed by.  The kind Xettiachio who came halfway across the world with a RTS to give him.  The stearn Chula who stood by and healed him while he was over his head against the monster beetles.  The kind Lashene who took him under her wing and patiently showed him how to get to and fight in Unrest.  And through it all was the everpresent help of his fellow shaman and leader Bearpaws.</P><P>The years passed quickly and the comrades of his youth the bard Bansidh and the barbarian warrior Nanoc soon joined the Order.   Also following him into the clan were his pet gnome sidekicks Peza and Neke.</P><P>The raids and hunts were to numerous to count, one running into another, and all the while Borlanis gained in experience and in the knowledge of what a shaman should be.  Unrest, Permafrost, Cazic Thule, PAW and Blackburrow were his training grounds.  And they served him well.  </P><P>Then the day came when he struck out on his own and followed a path that may not have been the wisest but provided him with the experience to learn new spells and he earned the right to a puppy, every barbarian shaman lads dream.  The bards of Norrath took a dim view of this and to this day, the name of Borlanis is still spoken in whispers wherever bards gather and the name is often used to frighten their children into obedience.  </P><P>Following his long war against the bards of Antonica he took his fight to certain dwarves of Burcherblock.  While he earned the animosity of that one sect, he gained a huge dwarven following as he re-distributed the wealth of that sect among many of the small dwarves who were just beginning to ply thier trade.</P><P>to be continued.....</font></td>
      </tr>

